It's day five of 21 families at Scenery Park in the Eastern Cape not knowing what killed their children. This is after an incident at a local tavern claimed the lives of these young people, the youngest is 13 years old. eNCA senior reporter Aviwe Mtila has more. Courtesy of #DStv403 EAST LONDON - Survivors of the Enyobeni tavern tragedy have come forward, detailing the horrific events that occurred hours before the 21 teenagers' bodies were discovered on Sunday. There's still no confirmation on the cause of death of these youngsters. READ: Tavern tragedy | No official word on cause of deaths There's been speculation that they may have inhaled carbon monoxide while inside the tavern. Families will be burying their loved ones at a mass funeral next week.